ğŸ”’ Security Architecture
API Protection: All critical backend routes are protected by the protect middleware. Financial operations, user management, and reporting routes require explicit validation via the isAdmin middleware.

Data Sanitization: Passwords are never sent back to the client. The backend specifically filters out password fields when returning user lists.

State Synchronization: The frontend securely stores the JWT token in localStorage and attaches it as a Bearer token to all Axios requests via an interceptor.

Atomic Transactions: Bulk sales in the POS loop through stock checks before deduction to ensure data integrity during concurrent checkouts.